Kidnappers have freed the supervisor working at the farm of a former governor of Oyo State, late Christopher Adebayo Alao-Akala. DAILY POST recalls that the supervisor was abducted on Saturday in the farm named TDB farms, located in Jabata, Surulere Local Government Area in Oyo State. The kidnappers had demanded for the sum of N100m as ransom. A close source to the Alao-Akala family confirmed the release of the kidnapped victim to DAILY POST Thursday morning. The source, in a telephone conversation with DAILY POST, said that the supervisor was released on Tuesday after the sum of N5m was paid as ransom.